        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-08-29 09:47:17.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Jian Yu",
          "email": "jian.yu@intel.com",
          "date": "2013-08-29 09:47:17.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-3027 clio: only match original lock request",
        "message": "LU-3027 clio: only match original lock request\n\nBy matching only originally requested region in sublock we\nare making sure to avoid the race where we match the expanded region,\nbut the uderlying ldlm lock gets cancelled by the time we have\na chance to reference it and then we end up reenqueuing the wrong lock.\n\nThis does have a downside of potentially creating more sublocks\nas a rolling write will not be able to match previous sublocks,\nbut this should not result in any extra RPCS because underlying ldlm lock\nwould still be matched (Assuming it's still there at the match time).\n\nTest-Parameters: envdefinitions=SLOW=yes,ONLY=write_disjoint \\\nclientdistro=el6 serverdistro=el6 clientarch=x86_64 \\\nserverarch=x86_64 testlist=parallel-scale\n\nChange-Id: I28b795a909e6a5f2f145f762b296c76b25a95c7d\nSigned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: Jian Yu <jian.yu@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
